ball.post_text: Zaheer: "Oh man! This IPL is making my head spin. Tilak retired out, Shami replaced before his quota used, and a few more decisions like that. Are there points to make IPL even more thrilling?"
ball.text: Hello, SKY! This is too full on leg and Suryakumar gets down to sweep it high over fine leg and into the stands
Suryakumar Yadav gets down to sweep and misses. This was a legbreak tossed full outside off. Surely impact was outside off and the ball would have likely missed the wickets as well
Full around middle, this one goes on with the angle. He backs away and punches it down the ground wide of long-on
Dropped a bit short outside off, slapped straight to the extra cover fielder
Inside edge goes past the stumps and races away! Legbreak on off, Jacks pushes at it and gets lucky
Tossed up on leg, SKY eases it out to long-on

comms.required_string: 81 runs required from 11 overs, RR: 9.11, RRR: 7.36

ball.pre_text: SKY back out in the middle for the second time in two overs. This time he will have to bat
ball.text: On a length outside off, tucked out through midwicket and gets a single to get off the mark immediately

ball.dismissal: RD Rickelton c Head b Patel 31 (23b 5x4 0x6) SR: 134.78
ball.text: Skied and taken! Rickelton's second life doesn't last long, but he has added some quick runs. Harshal bowls an offcutter wide of off, Rickelton reaches out as he looks to go inside out and gets an edge that goes up. Head at backward point backtracks and settles under it
Takes on the bouncer now! Dug in short and angled across Rickelton, and he has enough room to free his arms and pull it square

ball.pre_text: Ddn: "Replacing Shami?! Huh, so no last over from him" Clearly not. Mat Roller said he's gone and sat in the dugout, and looks to be fine. IF it is a fitness issue, we'll only know later
ball.text: Length ball on the pads and Rickelton says 'thank you very much'. Helps it along beyond square and it's in the gap for four
On a length outside off, swung away to deep midwicket

ball.pre_text:
Here is Harshal Patel to bowl. Meanwhile, Rahul Chahar is on as the impact player, replacing Mohammed Shami!

Mansoor: "Watching cricket for years and honestly had no idea that gloves in front of stumps constitutes a no-ball." Admittedly, I knew collecting the ball in front of the stumps would make it a no-ball, but this is new for me too!
ball.text: Very full outside off, driven along the carpet to long-off

comms.required_string: 93 runs required from 12 overs, RR: 8.75, RRR: 7.75

ball.post_text: A quiet over, but it could have been so much better for SRH!
ball.text: Tosses it up and it's a low full toss around off, pushed to extra cover
Tossed up wide of off and Rickelton slaps it out to long-off on the bounce

ball.pre_text: And now Rickelton gets a free hit too!
ball.text: Ansari looks to go wide and gets it beyond the wide line. So he'll have to bowl that again

Cummins holds on at cover! This is a rank long hop and Rickelton backs away to slap it away. It's gone to Cummins' right and he takes a nice catch diving to his right Scratch all that! Klaasen's gloves were in front of the stumps when Rickelton hits that, so it's a no-ball! SKY was out in the middle, Rickelton was back in the hut. And now he'll be back in the middle. One South African wicketkeeper giving another a reprieve! We saw the return crease no-ball from Starc yesterday, and today this! Zeeshan Ansari lets out a frustrated smile
Now Rickelton moves leg side and looks to slog it. It's the googly from Ansari and beats the outside edge
Length ball angled across, Rickelton gets an inside edge onto the ground as the ball squeezes out towards extra cover

ball.pre_text: Anurag: "Hands it over to Malinga had me confused thinking how can Malinga bowl against Mumbai Indians, then I remembered it is 2025 and not the 2015 era of Lasith Malinga!"
ball.text: Rickelton misses his sweep to this full ball around off. Mild appeal for lbw, but that was likely impact outside off, and hence also missing wickets

ball.pre_text: Zeeshan Ansari will get the first over outside the powerplay
ball.text: Starts off with a legbreak on a length on leg, Jacks goes back and tucks it out through midwicket

comms.required_string: 104 runs required from 13 overs, RR: 8.42, RRR: 8

ball.post_text:
Malli: "One Malinga owned Wankhede, other one hasn't had great start so far"

Shane: "How can ball needs to be changed just after 35 deliveries?!" Well, the umpire can choose to change the ball at any point if it's damaged, which is what I reckon happened. They were having a hard look at the seam.

That will be the timeout
ball.pre_text:
Tijo: "Not an optimist? Imagine scoring 50 in every innings for 20 years!" Yeah, okay, you've got me there!

Looks like the umpires are having a look at the ball. An official brings out a set of new balls, and they take one of those. Cummins has a look at it and hands it to Malinga

"@Vinay At this rate, Rohit reaches his century in 2048," chuckles Akhilesh, who is clearly not as much of an optimist!
ball.text: On a length outside off, Jacks looks to drive and gets a thick edge to short third on the bounce
Full outside off and angling in, Rickelton eases it out to deep square leg

ball.pre_text: ddn: "Rickleton should get a longer rope. He looks fine despite just one good score. Remember Pollard had gotten a huge rope in his debut IPL season." Exactly. He hasn't played a lot in these conditions before this.
ball.text: Lovely drive! Low full toss outside off and he creams it wide of the mid-off fielder
Two in a row for Ricks! This is a short ball that sits up nicely for him and he swings it away through square leg. Harshal running to his right from deep backward square can't stop that

ball.pre_text: Vinay Srivastav: "Has anyone noticed that Rohit Sharma is incrementally scoring more runs in every subsequent innings in this IPL? Is this a record (improving your highest score every next innings) 0,8,13,NA,17,18,26" Encouraging for Mumbai Indians, I suppose!
ball.text: Rickelton will feel much better now! He had been struggling so far but gets a hold of this! Slower ball, but in the slot around off, and he lofts it over mid-off
On a length outside off, tucked away to deep backward square

comms.required_string: 108 runs required from 14 overs, RR: 9.16, RRR: 7.71

ball.post_text: shravan: "Not impressed by Rickelton's performances so far except for that one half century...does MI have any other wicket keepers who can bat?" Robin Minz has failed to impress with the bat in the few appearances he got
ball.text: Head, what have you done? He's put down a sitter! Jacks slaps this length ball in front of point and it goes to Head's left at cover. Was a simple catch, but he lets the ball slip through his hands!
Jacks gets going! It's an offcutter but in the slot around off, Jacks backs away and flat-bats this straight of mid-off
On a length around off, Jacks clips it to midwicket
Swung away through square leg off the inside half as Ricke;ton continues to struggle to middle it. This was the offcutter from Shami

comms.required_string: 123 runs required from 15 overs, RR: 8, RRR: 8.2
